SIMPLE: frontlet
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frontlet
<hw>Front"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. frontelet brow
band, dim. of <ets>frontel</ets>, <ets>frontal</ets>. See
<er>Frontal</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A frontal or
brow band; a fillet or band worn on the forehead.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They shall be as <qex>frontlets</qex> between thine eyes.</q>
<rj><qau>Deut. vi. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A frown (likened to a frontlet).</def> <mark>[R. &
Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What makes that <qex>frontlet</qex> on? Methinks you are too much
of late i' the frown.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The margin of the head, behind
the bill of birds, often bearing rigid bristles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fronto-</ent>⟦br⟧
